'''Alfredo Mario Esp√≥sito Castro''' (20 May 1927 ‚Äì 1 January 2010) was the first [[Roman Catholic]] bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Z√°rate-Campana]], [[Argentina]].

Ordained to the priesthood for Institute of Consecrated Life [[Claretians]] on August 1, 1954, [[Pope Paul VI]] named Esp√≥sito Castro bishop on April 21, 1976 and he was ordained on 4 July 1976; he resigned on 18 December 1991.<ref>http://catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bespcas.html</ref>

