In Hindu mythology '''Dhanyamalini''' was the second wife of [[Ravana]]. She was a gentle and caring woman. Her true identity is unknown but some stories refer to her as the daughter of [[Mayasura|Maya]] and sister of [[Mandodari]], while others speak of her as a danava princess who was the sister-in-law of Meenakshi or [[Shurpanaka]]. She referred to have saved Sita from Ravana's rage when she insulted him. Dhanyamalini had two sons from Ravana, they were [[Atikaya]] and [[Trishira]].

