*{{note|ImƒÅm RidhƒÅ|A}} Capacity of one courtyard: 100,000; Total number courtyards: 7; Total shrine area: 267,079 m<sup>2</sup>; Total courtyard area: 331,578 m<sup>2</sup> (world's largest)
*{{note|Istiqlal|B}} Capacity, main building: 61,000; secondary building: 8,000; bridge building: ~1,000; Terrace: 50,000;
*{{note|Hassan II|C}} Capacity, inside: 25,000; outside: 80,000. Covered Area: 20,000 m<sup>2</sup>
*{{note|Faisal|D}} Capacity, hall: 10,000; [[portico]]es: 24,000; courtyard; 40,000. Covered Area: 5,000 m<sup>2</sup>
*{{note|Badshahi|E}} Capacity, hall: 5,000; courtyard and porticoes: 95,000. Courtyard area: 278,784 m<sup>2</sup>
*{{note|Sheikh Zayed|F}} Capacity, main prayer hall: 9,000; 2 halls for women: 2 * 1,500; porticoes: 18,000.
*{{note|Jama|G}} Capacity, hall: 10,000; courtyard: 75,000.
*{{note|Masjid|H}} Accommodates more than 1,000,000 during peak times
*{{note|Nabawi|I}} Plans announced in 2012 for expansion to accommodate two million worshippers by 2040.<ref name=Arabnews2012>{{cite news|title=Prophet‚Äôs Mosque to accommodate two million worshippers after expansion|url=http://www.arabnews.com/prophet%E2%80%99s-mosque-accommodate-two-million-worshippers-after-expansion|accessdate=27 November 2016|work=Arab News|date=26 September 2012|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307071616/http://www.arabnews.com/prophet%E2%80%99s-mosque-accommodate-two-million-worshippers-after-expansion|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
*{{note|pak_ahmadi|J}} This is an Ahmadiyya place of worship in Pakistan. While members of the [[Ahmadiyya]] movement regard themselves as Muslim, and this place is considered a mosque by those outside Pakistan, Ahmadiyya are legally classed as non-Muslims in Pakistan by the [[Second Amendment to the Constitution of Pakistan]] and therefore this is not considered a mosque in Pakistan, for legal purposes.
