==Awards== Bu√±uel was given the Career Golden Lion in 1982 by the [[Venice Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Golden Lion for Career Achievement |url=http://www.carnivalofvenice.com/the-city/events-in-venice/venice-film-festival/awards-and-acknowledgements/golden-lion/golden-lion-for-career-achievement?lang=en |website=Portale di Venezia |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref> and the [[International Federation of Film Critics|FIPRESCI Prize]] ‚Äì Honorable Mention in 1969 by the [[Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Berlinale - International Film Festival Berlin |url=https://www.inter-film.org/festivals/berlinale-international-film-festival-berlin |website=inter-film |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref> In 1977, he received the [[National Prize for Arts and Sciences]] for Fine Arts.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Salazar |first1=David |title=Famed Mexican Auteur Arturo Ripstein's 'Bleak Street' Gets US Run |url=https://www.latinpost.com/articles/104216/20151223/famed-mexican-auteur-arturo-ripsteins-bleak-street-gets-run.htm |website=Latin Post |accessdate=9 August 2018}}</ref> At the [[11th Moscow International Film Festival]] in 1979, he was awarded the Honorable Prize for his contribution to cinema.<ref name="Moscow1979">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1979 |title=11th Moscow International Film Festival (1979) |accessdate=20 January 2013 |website=MIFF |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403102012/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1979 |archivedate=3 April 2014 |df= }}</ref>
