==Monuments==
A number of ancient monuments in [[Mumbai]] and [[Kolhapur]] district pay tribute to this dynasty's prowess:
* The [[Walkeshwar Temple]] and the [[Banganga Tank]] were built during the reign of Chittaraja, a king of this dynasty.<ref>[http://www.gsbkonkani.net/TEMPLES/BANGANGA%20SHRI%20WALKESHWAR.htm Banganga, Walkeshwar history]</ref>
* The [[Shiv Mandir, Ambarnath]], also near Mumbai, was also built by Chittaraja in 1060
* [[Kopineshwar Mandir, Thane|Kopineshwar Mandir]], a Shiva temple in [[Thane]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://thanecity.gov.in/marathi/page.php?id=4 | title=‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§® ‡§∂‡•ç‡§∞‡•Ä‡§∏‡•ç‡§•‡§æ‡§®‡§ï ‡§§‡•á ‡§Ü‡§ß‡•Å‡§®‡§ø‡§ï ‡§†‡§æ‡§£‡•á ‡§∂‡§π‡§∞  |language=Marathi | publisher=''[[Thane Municipal Corporation]]'' | accessdate=8 August 2015}}</ref>
* [[Parshwanath]] [[Jain]] temple of Kolhapur Shilahars at Ibrahimpur and Bhogoli in [[Chandgad]] taluka.
* [[Parshwanath]] [[Jain]] temple of Kolhapur Shilahars at Ainapur in [[Gadhinglaj]] taluka.
* [[Parshwanath]] [[Jain]] temple of Kolhapur Shilahars at Baamni and Sangaon in [[Kagal]] taluka.

